oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Flooded Forked Deer River
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of high water levels along the Forked Deer River after a flood. Two buildings are visible in the distance. This photograph was taken at the south end of McClanahan's Levee in Jackson, Tennessee.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Rivers; Floods; Houses; Trees
